{"info": {"author": "Alex Barcelo", "author_email": "alex.barcelo@bsc.es", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# NumPy Persistence to Non-Volatile Memory\n\nThis library will help you persist numpy array structures into NVM devices.\n\nInternally, it uses [`pynvm`](https://github.com/pmem/pynvm) and buffers --which are\nnatively supported by `numpy`.\n\n## Installation\n\n`pip install npp2nvm`\n\n## Requirements\n\n - A NVM device, such as Intel(R) Optane(TM) DC Persistent Memory modules.\n - Python 3.x\n - numpy arrays to be stored.\n\n## Usage\n\nTwo environment variables are used for configuring the storage:\n\n - **NPP2NVM_SIZE** which specifies the size (in MiB) that will be assigned to\n persistence\n - **NPP2NVM_PATH** which specifies the file path that will be used for persistence.\n Note that this file should be located into a _Storage Class Memory_ device, which will\n allow `pynvm` to leverage its characteristics --keep in mind that `pynvm` are bindings of the \n [PMDK](https://pmem.io/pmdk/) libraries.\n\n## Example\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\nimport npp2nvm\n\na = np.random.random([256, 256])\na = npp2nvm.np_persist(a)\nprint(a.shape)\n# > (256, 256)\n```\n\n## Limitations\n\nStorage and retrieval of data structures (outside the application lifecycle) \nare not implemented in this library (yet?). You can implement your own \nmechanism and/or propose a PR. It will be appreciated!\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/bsc-dom/npp2nvm", "keywords": "pynvm nvm persistence numpy", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "npP2NVM", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/npP2NVM/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/npP2NVM/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/bsc-dom/npp2nvm"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/npP2NVM/0.2/", "requires_dist": ["pynvm"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "NumPy Persistence to Non-Volatile Memory", "version": "0.2", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>NumPy Persistence to Non-Volatile Memory</h1>\n<p>This library will help you persist numpy array structures into NVM devices.</p>\n<p>Internally, it uses <a href=\"https://github.com/pmem/pynvm\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>pynvm</code></a> and buffers --which are\nnatively supported by <code>numpy</code>.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p><code>pip install npp2nvm</code></p>\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>A NVM device, such as Intel(R) Optane(TM) DC Persistent Memory modules.</li>\n<li>Python 3.x</li>\n<li>numpy arrays to be stored.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>Two environment variables are used for configuring the storage:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>NPP2NVM_SIZE</strong> which specifies the size (in MiB) that will be assigned to\npersistence</li>\n<li><strong>NPP2NVM_PATH</strong> which specifies the file path that will be used for persistence.\nNote that this file should be located into a <em>Storage Class Memory</em> device, which will\nallow <code>pynvm</code> to leverage its characteristics --keep in mind that <code>pynvm</code> are bindings of the\n<a href=\"https://pmem.io/pmdk/\" rel=\"nofollow\">PMDK</a> libraries.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Example</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">numpy</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"nn\">np</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">npp2nvm</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">np</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">random</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">random</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"mi\">256</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">256</span><span class=\"p\">])</span>\n<span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">npp2nvm</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">np_persist</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">shape</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># &gt; (256, 256)</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>Limitations</h2>\n<p>Storage and retrieval of data structures (outside the application lifecycle)\nare not implemented in this library (yet?). You can implement your own\nmechanism and/or propose a PR. It will be appreciated!</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6894827, "releases": {"0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "6c6b519e5fe587a102f37b5c3b651694", "sha256": "e2024941d3a76a333f5b4dc57e8b5166d40f78c1ed3e282e399ea58752676568"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "npP2NVM-0.2-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "6c6b519e5fe587a102f37b5c3b651694", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 7135, "upload_time": "2020-03-27T09:25:24", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-27T09:25:24.135334Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/bf/0c/0e71e501832e90d775377627e9170901d8235dd7d06cf163b91e069a69e4/npP2NVM-0.2-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "4bb6ce4c49aa97904abe5759ff6884e0", "sha256": "4e324d86711ae06234a4c1ec849248bfb853d01e2f44bf785e8f63a0d6f770d9"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "npP2NVM-0.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "4bb6ce4c49aa97904abe5759ff6884e0", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2767, "upload_time": "2020-03-27T09:25:26", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-27T09:25:26.182549Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/32/e2/15d11aed2f6cb1